
[1]treatment

   TRE'ATMENT, n. Management; manipulation; manner of mixing or combining,
   of decomposing and the like; as the treatment of substances in chimical
   experiments.

   1. Usage; manner of using; good of bad behavior towards.

   Accept such treatment as a swain affords.

   2. Manner of applying remedies to cure; mode or course pursued to check
   and destroy; as the treatment of a disease.

   3. Manner of applying remedies to; as the treatment of a patient.
     __________________________________________________________________

